review_title: Good place to gain Security experience
job_title: Security Officer in Duluth, MN
pros:
Good co-workers 
Co-workers you can depend on to have your back when situations get tense 
okay pay
Fantastic Security manager 
Free uniforms (except pants and boots)
cons:
Terrible administration:

Since COVID-19 started, their true colors started to show. Proper PPE was not given to Security staff when the pandemic started because we "weren't considered essential employees". It took us about 5-6 months into the pandemic to actually be issued the PPE we needed. 

We deal with non-compliant people all time time and get no recognition for it . 

They refuse to give us the pay we deserve because "we are not a department that brings in money for the hospital". 

They refuse to give us the proper equipment to deal with violent individuals (cuffs, sprays, tazer) because they dont want the hospital to "have that sort of image" and also don't want to deal with the liability. 

There are a lot of other little things that could be added to the list, but i'd be writing a book at that point.

review_title: Review ofSt. Luke's Hospital Duluth, Minnesota
job_title: Cleaning Attendant in Duluth, MN
pros:
I have always enjoyed working at St. Luke's (and hospitals).  St. Luke's is very near my home and I can walk if necessary. I appreciate the health care and the feeling I get of accomplishment when I do a good job. Additionally, I made many friends, some of whom I still have lunch with.
     I always try to do the best job that I can and I feel Lori appreciated that. I work the way I'd want someone to work for me.
cons: I was aware that some individuals were critical of me for the effort I put into my work but Lori spoke to both of them.
